# Trial INDEX

List of numbered evidence artifacts. `scripts/new_trial.py` adds new
entries automatically. Ledger files may later cite these artifacts during
claim, capability, or explanation assessment.

## Entries

| trial_id | mode | evidence artifact | optional protocol link | artifact status | ledger assessment |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|

## Artifact-status legend

- `planned`: artifact is planned, notebook not created
- `in-progress`: artifact created, measurement not yet interpreted
- `complete`: observation and interpretation are recorded
- `parked`: blocked on upstream dependency
- `dropped`: judged not worth pursuing; reason recorded in decisions.md

An artifact can be complete without moving research state. The ledger
assessment column records whether `capability_map.md`,
`explanation_ledger.md`, or `decisions.md` later cites it.

## Order

Sequential numbering is for reviewability. Research state determines what
evidence is needed next; evidence artifacts do not own that state.
